{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Tightlip"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"How Environment Sourcing Works"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A common frustration with secret-via-env-var setups: the variable works in your shell, but Xcode can’t see it. Or it works locally but not in CI. Or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.zshenv"},{"text":" exports something fine, but ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xcodebuild"},{"text":" from a launcher doesn’t pick it up.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tightlip addresses this by sourcing your shell init file itself, in a controlled subshell, every build."}]},{"text":"The Algorithm","anchor":"The-Algorithm","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For each build, the plugin:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Sources the env file in a clean zsh subshell.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" By default this is "},{"code":"~\/.zshenv","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", sourced with "},{"code":"zsh -f","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (no startup files, no profile chain). The subshell captures the resulting environment as a snapshot."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Merges that snapshot with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProcessInfo.processInfo.environment"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — the build’s own environment, including Xcode Scheme env vars and CI job env vars."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Resolves per-key conflicts in favor of ","type":"text"},{"code":"ProcessInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":" A CI runner that explicitly exports ","type":"text"},{"code":"APP_API_KEY","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" overrides anything ","type":"text"},{"code":"~\/.zshenv","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" might have said.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The result: identical resolution regardless of how the build was launched. Xcode.app from Finder, Conductor, VS Code, ","type":"text"},{"code":"xcodebuild","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from Terminal — same env vars seen, same generated file.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Failure Modes","anchor":"Failure-Modes","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The subshell sourcing has a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"5-second timeout"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":". If sourcing fails (the file doesn’t exist, the file errors out, or it just takes too long), the tool falls back to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProcessInfo"},{"text":" alone and writes a single ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"note:"},{"text":" to stderr identifying the file.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This means CI runners with no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.zshenv"},{"type":"text","text":" work unchanged — the fallback kicks in immediately and the job’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"env:"},{"type":"text","text":" block is the sole source of values."}]},{"text":"Slow `.zshenv` Cases","anchor":"Slow-zshenv-Cases","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Tools like ","type":"text"},{"code":"mise","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"asdf","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"code":"direnv","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" invoked during ","type":"text"},{"code":".zshenv","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can push past the 5-second budget. If you see the ","type":"text"},{"code":"note: sourcing \/path\/to\/file ... using process environment only","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" message and weren’t expecting it, reproduce with:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["zsh -f -c 'source ~\/.zshenv'"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If that hangs or errors, your shell init is the cause. Move slow tools out of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".zshenv"},{"type":"text","text":" (into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".zshrc"},{"type":"text","text":", which the plugin doesn’t read), or point Tightlip at a smaller sidecar file with the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/EnvFileDirective","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"envFile directive","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"envFile directive"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/tightlipcore\/environmentsourcing"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/EnvironmentSourcing","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Why your env vars resolve the same way whether you build from Xcode, the terminal, or CI."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Related-Documentation","title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/EnvFileDirective","doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/GettingStarted"]},{"anchor":"Explanation","title":"Explanation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/Obfuscation"],"generated":true}],"references":{"doc://TightlipCore/documentation/TightlipCore/EnvFileDirective":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tightlipcore\/envfiledirective","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Point Tightlip at a different shell-init file with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"envFile:"},{"type":"text","text":" directive."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/EnvFileDirective","title":"Overriding the Sourced Env File"},"doc://TightlipCore/documentation/TightlipCore/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/GettingStarted","url":"\/documentation\/tightlipcore\/gettingstarted","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the plugin to a target, drop in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Secrets.yml"},{"type":"text","text":", and start reading secrets at compile time."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Getting Started with Tightlip"},"doc://TightlipCore/documentation/TightlipCore":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A SwiftPM build-tool plugin that generates a typed Swift "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Secrets"},{"type":"text","text":" enum from environment variables at build time."}],"title":"Tightlip","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/tightlipcore","role":"collection"},"doc://TightlipCore/documentation/TightlipCore/Obfuscation":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"What the XOR encoding actually protects against, and what it doesn’t."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/tightlipcore\/obfuscation","identifier":"doc:\/\/TightlipCore\/documentation\/TightlipCore\/Obfuscation","title":"Obfuscation and Threat Model","role":"article"}}}